%I A393561 #46 Mar 26 2026 00:03:19
%S A393561 13,229,241,13781,298693,80749767323
%N A393561 Smallest prime p such that p+1 starts a run of exactly n consecutive numbers having exactly the same number of divisors.
%e A393561 The 2 consecutive integers following the prime 13, namely [14, 15], all have the same number of divisors, namely 4; 16 has 5 divisors and no smaller integer following a prime displays this property, hence a(2) = 13.
%e A393561 The 3 consecutive integers following the prime 229, namely [230, 231, 232], all have the same number of divisors, namely 8; 233 has 2 divisors and no smaller integer following a prime displays this property, hence a(3) = 229.
%e A393561 a(5) = A119730(1).
%e A393561 a(6) = A119740(1).
%o A393561 (PARI) card(k)=my(n=numdiv(k+1),i=1);while(numdiv(k+i+1)==n, i++);i
%o A393561 a(n)=forprime(p=2,+oo,if(card(p)==n,return(p)))
%Y A393561 Cf. A119711, A119728, A119730, A119740.
%Y A393561 Cf. A005237, A006601, A006558, A049051, A049052, A049053.
%Y A393561 Cf. A067889, A391384.
%K A393561 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A393561 2,1
